{{Quote|You're too young to die? I'm too young to die!|Kazuda Xiono to R2-C4|<ref name="The Recruit" />}}
'''R2-C4''', frequently referred to as "'''C4'''," served the [[New Republic]] during [[34 ABY]] as an [[R2-series astromech droid|R2-series]] [[astromech droid]]. R2-C4 was a part of [[Kazuda Xiono]]'s [[Kazuda Xiono's team|squadron]] on their [[Mission to rendezvous with the Resistance|mission]] to deliver intel on the [[First Order]] to the [[Resistance]]. First Order [[pilot]] [[Major]] [[Baron]] [[Elrik Vonreg]] attacked the squadron, threatening to end the mission in failure. After [[Mia Gabon]] and [[Hugh Sion]], members of Xiono's squadron, made their escape to [[hyperspace]] Vonreg landed a hit on Xiono's and R2-C4's [[T-85 X-wing starfighter|X-wing]]. Resistance [[Commander]] [[Poe Dameron]] arrived in time to save Xiono and R2-C4. Working together, the New Republic members and Resistance commander were able to chase the First Order pilot away and complete the mission. When Xiono joined the Resistance for a [[Mission on the Colossus platform|mission]] on [[Castilon]], R2-C4 remained with the Resistance.

==Biography==
[[File:R2-C4-CGSWG.png|thumb|270px|left|R2-C4 in the droid socket of Xiono's T-85 X-wing fighter]]
R2-C4,<ref name="Ultimate SW" /> also known as "C4," was a [[New Republic]] [[astromech droid]] that operated<ref name="The Recruit" /> approximately [[34 ABY|thirty]]<ref name="Date">{{ResistanceDate|1|1}}</ref> [[Standard year|years]] after the [[Battle of Endor]]. R2-C4 accompanied a New Republic [[Kazuda Xiono's team|squadron]], led by [[pilot]] [[Kazuda Xiono]], on their [[Mission to rendezvous with the Resistance|mission]] to deliver intel to [[Resistance]] [[Commander]] [[Poe Dameron]]. R2-C4 rode in the [[astromech socket]] of Xiono's [[T-85 X-wing starfighter]]. Xiono's [[squadron]] was attacked by [[First Order TIE fighter pilot|First Order TIE Fighter Pilot]] [[Major]] [[Baron]] [[Elrik Vonreg]]. Xiono informed R2-C4 that he did not know where Dameron was but was certain he would arrive soon. Due to the danger, Xiono gave the command for the rest of the squadron, pilots [[Mia Gabon]] and [[Hugh Sion]], to retreat back to [[Republic High Command|base]] while he delivered the intel.<ref name="The Recruit" />

After Gabon and Sion fled the scene, Vonreg landed a shot on Xiono's [[X-wing starfighter|X-wing]]. Xiono requested confirmation that his squadmates successfully jumped to [[hyperspace]] and cheered at R2-C4's response, but soon discovered his X-wing's power was down. Dameron arrived to save the New Republic pilot and droid by blasting incoming [[warhead]]s and drawing Vonreg's attention. Xiono instructed R2-C4 to give him control of the weapons. Xiono requested Dameron lead the [[First Order]] pilot towards him. Dameron lead Vonreg towards Xiono and pulled away to let Xiono open fire and damage [[Elrik Vonreg's TIE Interceptor|Vonreg's]] [[TIE/ba Baron Space Superiority Interceptor|TIE]]. Vonreg was forced to retreat before Dameron could finish him off.<ref name="The Recruit" />

[[File:DameronAndXiono-TheRecruitPart1.png|thumb|right|270px|Poe Dameron and Kazuda Xiono talk while BB-8 and R2-C4 observe]]
With the fight over, Dameron instructed Xiono to come abroad and the Resistance would fix his ship. A [[Unidentified CR90 corvette (Resistance)|CR90 corvette]] appeared out of hyperspace that Xiono and R2-C4 boarded. Onboard they met with [[BB-series astromech droid|BB unit]] [[BB-8]] and Dameron. When Dameron left to speak with [[General]] [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]] a flustered Xiono requested Dameron tell Organa he said hello. The droids commented amongst themselves to which Xiono requested them to stop the commentary and show him where the [[refresher]] was. While Xiono refreshed himself BB-8 left to speak to Dameron, which Xiono discovered after he emerged from the refresher. Xiono asked R2-C4 which way BB-8 went and then insisted he would have a look around. He instructed R2-C4 to remain behind&mdash;an order the droid ignored.<ref name="The Recruit" />

Xiono agreed to join the Resistance and Dameron assigned him a [[Mission on the Colossus platform|mission]] on [[Castilon]].<ref name="The Recruit" /> R2-C4 was left with the Resistance, becoming a member of the organization.<ref name="Ultimate SW" />

==Characteristics==
R2-C4 was manufactured by [[Industrial Automaton]]. The droid had a [[Color|blue]] chassis with gray, white, and yellow plating. A light blue sensor was located on the droid's dome.<ref name="Ultimate SW" />

==Behind the scenes==
R2-C4 was first pictured in a trailer to introduce [[Team Fireball|Team ''Fireball'']], featured alongside concept art of Kazuda Xiono.<ref name="Fireball">{{SWYouTube|dlucTaqVVcs|Meet Team Fireball &#124; Star Wars Resistance|sw_url=video/meet-team-fireball-star-wars-resistance}}</ref> R2-C4 appeared in the first part of the two-part episode "[[The Recruit]],"<ref name="The Recruit" /> the [[Star Wars Resistance Season One|premiere]] of the television series ''[[Star Wars Resistance]]'', which premiered on [[October 7]], [[2018]].<ref name="Resistance trailer">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-resistance-trailer|text=''Star Wars Resistance'' Trailer Revealed}}</ref> R2-C4 was only referred to as "C4" in the episode<ref name="The Recruit" /> but received full designation as R2-C4 in the [[2019]] reference book ''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''.<ref name="Ultimate SW" />

